    • Constructor Detail

      • QoSResult

        @Since(value="7.0")
public QoSResult(Long minIOPS,
                    Long maxIOPS,
                    Long burstIOPS,
                    Long burstTime,
                    Object curve)
        Quality of Service (QoS) Result values are used on SolidFire volumes to provision performance expectations.
        Parameters:
        minIOPS - [required] Desired minimum 4KB IOPS to guarantee.
        maxIOPS - [required] Desired maximum 4KB IOPS allowed over an extended period of time.
        burstIOPS - [required] Maximum "peak" 4KB IOPS allowed for short periods of time.
        burstTime - [required] The length of time burstIOPS is allowed.
        curve - [required] The curve is a set of key-value pairs.
        Since:
        7.0

    • Method Detail

      • getMinIOPS

        public Long getMinIOPS()
        Desired minimum 4KB IOPS to guarantee. The allowed IOPS will only drop below this level if all volumes have been capped at their minIOPS value and there is still insufficient performance capacity.

      • getMaxIOPS

        public Long getMaxIOPS()
        Desired maximum 4KB IOPS allowed over an extended period of time.

      • getBurstIOPS

        public Long getBurstIOPS()
        Maximum "peak" 4KB IOPS allowed for short periods of time. Allows for bursts of I/O activity over the normal maxIOPS value.

      • getBurstTime

        public Long getBurstTime()
        The length of time burstIOPS is allowed. The value returned is represented in time units of seconds.
        NOTE: this value is calculated by the system based on IOPS set for QoS.

      • getCurve

        public Object getCurve()
        The curve is a set of key-value pairs. The keys are I/O sizes in bytes. The values represent the cost performing an IOP at a specific I/O size. The curve is calculated relative to a 4096 byte operation set at 100 IOPS.
